[SN]TITLE[SN]
Floyd Ayite: Fulham bring in Togo forward from Bastia

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Championship side Fulham have signed Togo international Floyd Ayite from French Ligue 1 side Bastia for an undisclosed fee.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 27-year-old forward has agreed a three-year contract at Craven Cottage, with the Whites having an option to extend the deal by a further 12 months.
France-born Ayite began his career at Bordeaux and has also had loan spells at Angers and Nancy.
He joined Reims in the summer of 2011 and then moved on to Bastia in 2014.
Ayite is Fulham's second signing of the transfer window following the arrival of defender Michael Madl in May.
